+//! Tier-1 Jepsen consistency harness orchestration helpers (proposal 0005 §13.2,
+//! `0005:408`, issue #250): the **host-independent** part of the Tier-1 Jepsen harness —
+//! the in-repo harness directory path — so this logic is unit-testable without
+//! `lein`, a live cluster, or privileged I/O (ADR-0016).
+//!
+//! The privileged scenario that uses the real Jepsen/Elle cluster lives at `jepsen/`
+//! and is invoked via `lein run test`; `cargo xtask jepsen` runs it via
+//! `faults::run_jepsen` in the off-Check Tier-1 CI job (`tier1-jepsen.yml`), opted
+//! in by `WYRD_TIER1=1`.
+//!
+//! # Born-at-tier flippable coverage
+//!
+//! `xtask/tests/jepsen_orchestration.rs` imports these helpers and tests them
+//! without any JVM/lein/cluster. When a helper is removed or returns a wrong value,
+//! those tests go RED inside `cargo xtask ci` — the "deferred ≠ unbuilt" bar (the
+//! Verification-posture forcing function from `templates/brief.md.tpl` and INTEGRATION
+//! §"Deferred/off-Check tiers").
+
+/// Path to the in-repo Jepsen harness directory (the Clojure/lein project at
+/// `jepsen/` under the workspace root). Pure and unit-testable without `lein`
+/// or a live cluster.
+///
+/// This replaces the old `WYRD_TIER1_JEPSEN_CMD` external-command lookup with a
+/// fixed in-repo path, mirroring how `run_disk_faults` dispatches to the in-repo
+/// `crates/custodian/tests/tier1_disk_faults.rs` scenario rather than reading an
+/// env-var shell string (pre-#195 pattern, now closed for this leg too).
+#[must_use]
+pub fn jepsen_harness_dir(workspace_root: &std::path::Path) -> std::path::PathBuf {
+    workspace_root.join("jepsen")
+}
